<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hiya, hiya. Whadya need today?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; A short middle-aged gentleman asks as you walk in. He gestures around him, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Is there anything, anything, I can get for you.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
You look, you wander, and you glance around. &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gee my grandpa's attic wasn't this bad!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; As continue turning gathering in the slapdash clutter of the place you wonder how the grapevine could have been so wrong about this being &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> the place</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; to find what you are looking for so desperately.<br>
<br>
When you start looking for the exit the shopkeeper blows the dust off of a wardrobe standing to one-side, obviously groping for the handle.  During it's brief opening you see inside a complete set of plate mail that sparkles as if the smith just finished the last touches.<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ya know you'll catch flies with that</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;, he reaches up, pats the underside of your chin, closing your mouth for you. &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I have the best selection of almost anythin', sometimes everythin', in this here town.  Everyone comes and gives me first offer on loot and treasure and those odd I-don't-know's that they find when on the road, even when under them there roads.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I generally give best price to buy things, I like know'in everyone can come to me, and I give a very minor mark up on things as well.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; His voice takes on an oily manner;   &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> All your needs are my concerns.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Now I see that look in your eye.  No I can't get you everythin' but if I don't have it I might know someone who would.  And if I don't someone who would I can at least tell you where's the best place to ask.  I don't just sell equipment mind you.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
Your curiosity peaked you start really looking over all the displayed wares with a critical eye. As you do so you try your hardest to figure out what half of the items could be and what the other half might be.<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Now I have to admit that I don't always believe where everyone says they got somethin', sometimes the stories I hear are just a tad bit wild.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; He gives you a curious look, then he gestures over towards a dimmed section of the shop, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Like for instance take a look at this here fine dragonhide belt.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> See now, this here lil guy comes in and says how much for this.  Well I look at it and figure not a whole lot right?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; He pushes his forefinger against the side of his nose while his eyes light up with mischief, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Of course I was a thinkin' to myself he'd be wanting a favor of my not member'in who I got it from, right? And them type of favors cost I'll tell you. Integrity is downright expensive in this here town!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> But then he puts it on and picks up that there wardrobe like it was nutt'in. Well give him my let's get this doggie going look and we starts a haggl'in.  He's acclaiming that he not only had the belt made but killed and skinned the dragon just last week and I know he sold a lil something on the sly three days past.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> So I looks real close and notice just how familiar it was and mentioned it. Well whadya know the price drops right fast at that point.  You might say I got it for a steal.  Heh-heh, steal get it.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ahh, I see that you're a might interested in it. Well how's about 600 crown for it?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
You think about his reputation and seriously debate your next statements. However finding no other choice you relate to him your story minus one or two salient, and possibly embarrassing, details.<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ahh, tis a story I have heard all to often in this town. With the look on your face I should have known.  It is nice indeed-y that all them there adventurous types told you where to find me. I think I can help out a decent fellow such as yerself who is trying to do right by a </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;friend&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> .  How about 300 crown?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
He quickly holds up one hand in front you as your shoulders swell from indignation, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> No funny stuff or I'll tell everyone how you gave me trouble and you don't want that do you? No? Good, I'm glad you heard how well loved I am, or at least, how needed I am.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
You grimace as you really have no choice. However your sense of satisfaction is mollified by the grim demeanor that your hard earned money to this leech.<br>
<br>
 As you turn to leave he reaches out and grabs your arm, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Now remember Louie's policies. If anyone asks where you got that, and anything else you might buy, you proudly tell them </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> At Phukivyno's, where everything's gotta go and fast</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->'.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Oh and by the way I charged you an extra hundred because you didn't tell me the belt was really yours in the first place. Have a nice day.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
