Description of Site and Proprietor: <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Louie is a fence but he prefers to only work with adventurers. He knows that most of them are usually selling things that are hard to find a fair price for.  And knowing how thorough most adventurers are he can also be sure that the owner isn't coming by later in the day.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Louie has sold things, and loose interpretation on things, to many groups of adventurers.  He has actually come to enjoy providing for their needs.  He will not, almost ever, sell to anyone else but an adventuring party or person.  The only exceptions to the rule is a couple of retired adventurers in town and, unfortunately, to the licensed members of any guild in town.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Why unfortunately is the case?  Well selling to a mage from the guild is one thing.  Selling to one of the Thieves or Assassin guild members can be quite another. Louie happily pays any &quot;protection&quot; fees associated with doing business in town.  He can usually count on getting a discount from being a retired guild member.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Louie's Shop is actually a marvel in terms of merchant skills and magic.  The house itself will not allow anyone to enter with &quot;ill&quot; thoughts towards Louie or his concerns.  The must stay outside until Louie asks them to enter (like the old vampire legends).  Some of the chests and containers will only open for Louie, or anyone wearing what appears to be his wedding ring (he's happily widowed), and they will actually, while closed, repair items till they look like new.  Note look like new, it will not recharge magic items in any way.  It will however return weapons and armor to like-new condition over time (Depending on GM's taste), and maybe even upgrading to masterwork material as well.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Louie will always warn adventurer's about anything he sells.  He can't be cured with an item while inside the shop &quot;as I can not always be certain what anything really is...&quot; so &quot;as-is&quot; definitely comes into play in his life.  Louie does however have one chest that 50% of the time will identify an item, 5% of the time determine charges and finally 1% time command words and curses.  Caveat Emptor I believe are two words that Louie can not spell but he knows them very well.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Last but not least Louie will always give a fair shake, that is to nice people. Anyone that gives him grief will almost always find just some little thing wrong with their purchase, usually just when they need it.  &quot;Ahh, a band of ogres. Will I'll just point my Staff of the Magi and..... Eeeeek!  That was the only charge!&quot;<br>
<br>
Gamemaster notes:<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Louie is the place where adventurer's can find that little thing that maybe they are looking for, if you wish to be nice.  Or that little thing they might happen to need, be it an item or information.  I have never really gotten as detailed in the physical aspects of Louie's shop becuase as an NPC &quot;we&quot; have a lot of latitude with him and his wares. In past history I have never had to roll one combat swing for him and wouldn't bother with keeping a complete adherent track of his stats because he is, in reality, just window dressing for the campaign.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Personality note: When I run Louie I think and try (hope I succeed) in portraying a medieval &quot;Leo Gets from Lethal Weapon type of character&quot;.<br>
